How to Create Admin User - Complete Guide
I've created multiple methods for you to create admin users:

Method 1: Run Admin Creation Script (Easiest)
bash
node create-admin.js
This will create an admin user with:

Email: admin@aeko.com
Username: admin
Password: admin123
Privileges: Full admin + golden tick
Method 2: API Endpoint for First Admin (No Auth Required)
json
POST /api/admin/setup/first-admin
{
  "name": "Admin User",
  "username": "admin",
  "email": "admin@aeko.com", 
  "password": "admin123"
}
This endpoint only works when no admin exists yet.

Method 3: Make Existing User Admin
json
POST /api/admin/admins/create
{
  "email": "existing-user@example.com",
  "permissions": ["read", "moderate", "manage"]
}
Method 4: Direct Database Update
If you have an existing user like milli.millihub@gmail.com:

json
POST /api/admin/admins/create
{
  "email": "milli.millihub@gmail.com"
}
